Gochujang Scrambled Eggs

Be the first to rate & review!
1 Photo

These gochujang scrambled eggs are both sweet and savory, and the Korean chile paste adds just the right amount of spice. I like to take it up a notch by adding deli ham.

By
Yolanda Gutierrez
Yolanda Gutierrez
Yoly loves to cook and bake and is an avid member of the Allrecipes Allstars, where she has shared countless original recipes and food photos.
Allrecipes' editorial guidelines
Published on July 21, 2025
Prep Time:
5 mins
Cook Time:
5 mins
Total Time:
10 mins
Servings:
1
Cook Mode (Keep screen awake)

Ingredients

  • 2 large eggs

  • 1 tablespoon heavy whipping cream

  • 1 tablespoon gochujang (Korean chili paste)

  • 1/2 tablespoon butter

  • 2 slices deli ham, cut into 1-inch pieces (optional)

  • salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste

  • sliced green onions (optional)

Directions

  1. Whisk eggs, heavy cream, and gochujang in a bowl. Set aside.

  2. Melt butter in a skillet. Add egg mixture and ham,, and cook and stir until eggs are scrambled and cooked. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with green onions.
